    "Productize selected district details for player-facing terrain/economic traits, population, labor, grain, cash, route status, governance, appointment state, actions, effects, and unavailable reasons.",
    "District lists remain secondary browsers with search, filter, sort, folding, rendering bounds or virtualization, and map/selection synchronization where existing read models support it.",
